In other cases, the information could not be used because of different legal regulations in the two member states.
In some cases, the financial management of another member state refused to provide information.
Some cases have been uncovered in which taxable persons in their summary notifications are not in the wrong position.
In the result, the data in mias were accordingly flawed, so that the clerks (the fä) had to determine in these cases (SEE 6).
