Comparison and evaluation
The situation in the two states is different.
While in Germany entrepreneurs are registered regardless of the amount of their turnover, the Czech Republic is the first requirement for registration (next to others) to exceed the threshold amount mentioned in the legislation.
If an entrepreneur does not exceed this threshold, he will be able to register voluntarily.
The registration process in Germany is standardized, but there may be differences due to different organisational structures in the individual federal states.
In the Czech Republic, the taxable person receives a tax number at the time of his first registration for any tax.
In the case of its registration for VAT, this tax number also applies to intra-community transactions.
In Germany, an entrepreneur who is registered for non-profit purposes receives a tax number exclusively for non-profit transactions.
If the German entrepreneur wants to carry out intra-community transactions, he must specifically allocate a VAT payment card. Request.
