Comparison and evaluation
Although in this report it is not possible to treat the specific criteria of the rms in Czech and Germany, however, the nku and the brh have found that each member state has developed its own RMS.
As well as the different approaches in the three above-mentioned German Federal States, the rms of each European State has its special strengths and weaknesses.
There is currently an exchange of experiences between the tax authorities of the European member states on new trends and new models of cross-Border Sales.
The fraud - especially the carousel - has proved to be not a national but European problem.
The people involved in fraud coordinate their actions not only in one, but in several member states.
A member state alone cannot develop an effective RMS.
Successful criteria, components or approaches for a rms must be exchanged and implemented in each EC member state. If this does not happen, scammers are looking for the member state with the weakest rms for their crimes.
The fraud caused by Europe-wide fraud in vat does not necessarily affect the member state in which the initiator is resident.
Any other member state that is involved in fraud may be affected.
That's why there should be a European exchange of experiences on the RMS.
