Both Czech taxable persons took account of the above deliveries in accordance with the Czech law no. 2004 in force. 235/2004 in their zm.
In a further examination of these transactions, a audit of the nku found that in 2004 different statutory regulations on delivery or delivery were made. The acquisition of electric energy between the Czech Republic and Germany was considered.
While in the Czech Republic, the taxable persons are supplying electrical energy according to the provisions of law no 2004 valid in 2004 235/2004 as an intra-Community Trade Fair, according to the German legislation in force in 2004, it was not an intra-community acquisition of goods, but about taxable and taxable sales in Germany.
The differences in the statutory regulations were made in the Czech Republic by adopting the law no. 635/2004 eliminated, which has changed some tax provisions with effect from 1. January 2005
23. in the examination of intra-community deliveries or acquisitions in cooperation with the brh were further found that a Czech taxable person in his zm for the first and fourth quarter of 2005 Intra-community deliveries to a German taxable person with a total value of 240.411.163 czk and another czech taxable person in his zm for the same period of intra-community deliveries to another german taxable person, worth 263.470.776 czk.
Information provided by the brh to the nku showed that in both cases it was about deliveries of electric energy.
In accordance with the wording of the law no. 1. January 2005 235/2004 is the place of performance for the delivery of electric energy to the place where the acquirer has its legal seat, its place of business or its establishment, for which this delivery is made.
That's why Czech taxpayers should not have indicated the electricity in their zm for 2005
